# H1 — Frame

> A rectangular cardboard frame worn around the head that redefines the perceived boundary of the skull, disrupting peripheral vision framing and altering how the wearer turns to look at things.

**Body region:** head
**Build time:** 15–20 minutes

---

## Parts required

Cut and lay out all parts before beginning assembly.

| Qty | Part | Material | Dimensions | Notes |
|-----|------|----------|------------|-------|
| 2 | Side panel | Double-wall cardboard | 30 × 25 cm | Left and right faces of the frame |
| 1 | Top panel | Double-wall cardboard | 30 × 20 cm | Bridges the two side panels |
| 1 | Front panel | Double-wall cardboard | 20 × 15 cm | Partial front face — open at the bottom for face |
| 2 | Handle tube | Narrow tube (Ø 2–3 cm) | 18 cm long | One each side, for the wearer to hold during fitting |
| — | Packing tape | — | ~1.5 m | Structural joints |
| — | Masking tape | — | ~1 m | Edge protection, comfort padding |

